{
  "answer": "In Allama Iqbal's *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, Chapter 23 (\"Swami Ram Tirath\"), the Muslim poet praises the Hindu sannyasi Swami Ram Tirath with these couplets fusing the Islamic *shahada* (\"Lā ilāha illā Allāh\") into a pearl-diving image, paired with the Abrahamic idol-smashing motif:\n\n> The negation of being is a wonder of the knowing heart;  \n> In the river of 'La' lies hidden the pearl of 'illa-Allah'.[^1]\n\n> The Abraham of Love shatters the idol of the Self;  \n> The remedy for reason is the ecstasy of Love's Tasnim.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/23-swami-ram-tirath/translation/#p-ef7cac).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/23-swami-ram-tirath/translation/#p-7de605).",
